    </div><!-- /.navbar-collapse -->
  </div><!-- /.container-fluid -->

</nav>
  <br />
  <div id="Mcsh" tabindex="-1" class="modal fade" role="dialog">
  <div class="modal-dialog bgcolor">
    <div class="modal-content ">
    <div class="modal-header">
      {% trans %}<strong>Help!</strong>{% endtrans %}
   <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button> </div>
      <div class="modal-body" style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;">

       <p>   <font color=" #566573"> {%trans%}

This screen provides you with three options: Create Organization, Select Organizations and Select Language. <br>
If you are running GNUKhata for the first time then Create Organization Tab will be active by default.</br>
You can choose language at any time. Presently GNUKhata has English (default), Marathi and Malayalam languages.
	 In this module you have to enter the name of organization, choose it's type (Profit Making or Not for Profit ) and then enter the financial year.
	 You can select 4 modes of operations varying in the number of features they provide. The least features comes in the accounting only option. Choose this if you only wish to maintain books of account.
	 Choose the invoicing only 
Note that you can use enter key to move to the next field and up arrow to move to earlier field.
Tab and Shift tab options are also available by default for navigation.</br>
Next screen will allow you to create admin user.
Select Organization from the dropdown and press enter.
Now choose financial year and press enter.
Login screen will appear after this.{% endtrans %} </font>

        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
  <div class="container-fluid" id="ticker">
    <ul class="shadow" style="list-style-type: none; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: -30px; padding: 0; overflow: hidden; background-color: rgb(248,248,248); height: 20px; border-radius: 5px;">
